            Published 8:16 p.m. CT Jan. 28, 2015 | Updated 9:05 a.m. CT Jan. 29, 2015Two multi-family buildings would be built in the area behind the parking garage of the Youth Opportunity Center on Charlotte Avenue, which houses nonprofit groups such as Oasis Center.(Photo: Submitted)Story HighlightsShmerling family seeks rezoning of site at Pearl and Fisk streets to allow 50 one-bedroom units in two multifamily buildings.
            
